<p>
<seg id=1> Audiences, let's look at the situations in China. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=2> The Chinese government has recently arrested some dissidents in order to block the gathering for some Chinese Democratic Party members in Zhejiang and Shanghai. </seg>
<seg id=3> Please listen to the report from VOA Chinese division, broadcast by Qing Yue. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> News from the Information center of Human Right and Democratic Movement in China which is headquartered in Hong Kong shows that public security officers in Hangzhou city caught two members of the Chinese Democratic Party Zhu Zhengming and Mao Qingxiang from their homes Friday afternoon. </seg>
<seg id=5> So far their whereabouts is still unclear. </seg>
<seg id=6> Before that, police has already detained another four mainstay of the Democratic movement who is closely connected with Chinese Democratic Party. They are Yao Zhengxian, Li Guotao, Wu Yilong and Wang Rongqing. </seg>
<seg id=7> The Information center of Human Right and Democratic Movement in China says that almost 20 members of the Chinese Democratic Party who from different divisions in Zhejiang and Shanghai originally planned to hold their first meeting in a hotel in Hangzhou city. </seg>
<seg id=8> The police took this action of arrestment according to the meeting. </seg>
<seg id=9> Besides, public security officers from other part of Zhejiang Province warned other active members of the democratic movement not to walk out doors, otherwise they will be arrested. </seg>
<seg id=10> The Chinese government sees the opposition party Chinese Democratic Party as illegal organization. It has detained and investigated a couple of the supporters and active members of this organization. </seg>
<seg id=11> But in most cases, they are released soon. </seg>
<seg id=12> CNN had reported respectively the newest situations announced by the Information center of Human Right and Democratic Movement in China. </seg>
</p>
